Global Funds Buy Net 8.17 Billion Rupees of India Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-02-17T03:39:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/global-funds-buy-net-8-17-billion-rupees-of-india-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 8.17
billion rupees ($180 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.7 percent to 1.05 trillion rupees, or 33.5
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign investors sold a net 2.3 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
